        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 1:31PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 131 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Woolum, or 13 miles south of Marshall, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hanover...                        Parma...
Rushing...                        Kay...
Turkey Creek...                   Rocky Hill...
Dennard...                        Botkinburg...
Crabtree...                       Shirley...
Brewer...                         Edgemont...
Elba...                           Oxley...
Hill Creek Recreation Area...     Fairfield Bay...
Woolum...                         Chimes...
Imo...                            Greers Ferry...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
